    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Serverless runs code without managing servers — platforms scale instances automatically and charge per invocation or compute time. For agents, serverless fits event-driven webhooks, lightweight tool handlers, and bursty API layers; long multi-minute agent loops often need containers or adjusted timeout limits."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Functions-as-a-Service (FaaS) — AWS Lambda, Google Cloud Functions, Azure Functions — execute handlers triggered by HTTP, queues, or schedules. Serverless containers (Cloud Run, Azure Container Apps scale-to-zero) run Docker images with similar pay-per-use models. You supply code; the platform manages OS patching and scaling."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# AWS Lambda handler (API Gateway trigger)\ndef handler(event, context):\n    body = json.loads(event.get(\"body\") or \"{}\")\n    run_id = enqueue_agent_job(body[\"prompt\"])\n    return {\"statusCode\": 202, \"body\": json.dumps({\"run_id\": run_id})}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Webhook receivers and async job enqueue endpoints need low ops and automatic scale on spike traffic. Serverless avoids paying for idle EC2 when agent usage is intermittent. Pair Lambda with SQS and Fargate workers: serverless front door, container workers for long LLM runs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "No server management",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — no patching Kubernetes nodes for simple handlers"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Auto scale",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — concurrent invocations match demand"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Pay per use",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — cheap at low volume"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Event integration",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — native SQS, EventBridge, Pub/Sub triggers"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fast deploy",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — small function updates in seconds"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Timeout limits",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
